{
  "stem": "20089.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Unfortunately, soon after, the Polish government closed their borders so that the Jewish Agency could not take the parents out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And they were left to work in the camps with the children.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My first role was to settle the children in the camps, and then to open nursery schools for the very young, schools for the school-going children, ORT workshops for the adults.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To teach the people a trade-- how to-- tailoring, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] carpentry, shoemaking-- the kind of skills or the kind of crafts that one wasn't used to having in the-- you know, in the ghettos-- or rather, in Siberia.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm not sure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But those were the workshops that ORT in America or the AJDC opened for these people-- carpentry workshops, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] shoe-- shoe, tanneries, shoemaking, sewing-- a lot of sewing was done by the women-- and leatherwork.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm not sure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we have ORT in South Africa too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that also deals with teaching-- vocational guidance.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I associate ORT with vocational guidance.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that stage, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- the impact came when I first arrived in Munich with my uncle.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was a-- a tremendous trauma and impact because those people had been survivors of the camps, whereas the children in the displaced person camps were not survivors in the sense that they were in concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had spent most of their lives in Siberia, and so they weren't so traumatized.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the-- the madrichim that were in charge of them were often from-- from Palestine.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were very sympathetic and very good with them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were mainly late teenagers or early-- in the early 20's and 30's, and they had a very good relationship.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they acted, I would say, as jolly good parent substitutes.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
